  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ 425°F/ Gas 7</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Cut the<strong> courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into batons </p>\n<p>Chop the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges, leaving the skins on (this helps them cook quicker)</p>\n<p>Trim the green stalk off the<strong> aubergine<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> and cut lengthways into wedges  </p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>baby plum tomatoes</strong>, <strong>chopped courgette</strong>, <strong>red onion</strong> and <strong>aubergine </strong>to a baking tray</p>\n<p>Drizzle with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and the <strong>harissa paste </strong>and give it a good mix up</p>\n<p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until softened and golden</p>\n<p>Once done, cut off the <strong>onion root</strong> to remove the skins</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, heat a dry pot over a high heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until golden and toasted</p>\n<p>Tip: watch the seeds like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>\n<p>Once done, transfer them to a plate and set aside, reserving the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> to the reserved pot with plenty of <span class=\"text-highlight\"><strong>boiled water</strong> </span>and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> (the same as you <span class=\"text-highlight\">would for pasta) </span></p>\n<p><span class=\"text-highlight\">Cook over</span> a high heat for 10-15 min or until tender with a slight bite, then drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1742.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
